yes, I understand, but my father's quirk also had its sideeffects. It was not so much his inability to memorize, say, his house numberin Boston, which was 68 and which he saw every day, but the fact that hecould do nothing about it; that nobody, but nobody could explain why all hecould make out at the far end of his brain was not 68 but a bottomlesshole."

